  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Boil half a kettle</p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) your<strong> garlic</strong></p><p>Chop your <strong>tomato[es] </strong>roughly</p><p>Deseed your<strong> pepper[s]</strong> (scrape the seeds and pith out with a teaspoon) and dice</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1654600728434-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1654600728434-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1654600728434-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1654600728434-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1654600728434-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large pot with a generous drizzle of<strong> olive oil</strong> over a medium heat</p><p>Once hot, add your <strong>ground smoked paprika</strong>, <strong>ground cumin </strong>and <strong>chopped garlic</strong> and cook for 30 secs</p><p>Add the<strong> diced pepper</strong>, <strong>chopped tomato</strong> and<strong> chipotle paste</strong> (can't handle the heat? Go easy!) and cook for 2-3 min or until the pepper is beginning to soften</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1654600736312-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1654600736312-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1654600736312-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1654600736312-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1654600736312-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, drain and rinse your <strong>black beans</strong></p><p>Dissolve your <strong>vegetable stock mix</strong> in 100ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[150ml] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[200ml]</span> <strong>boiled water </strong>with your <strong>tomato paste </strong>and a pinch of <strong>sugar</strong></p><p>Add the <strong>drained black beans </strong>to the pot with the tomato and cook for 5-8 min or until the sauce has thickened – these are your <strong>spicy beans</strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1654600740884-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1654600740884-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1654600740884-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1654600740884-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1654600740884-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, chop most of your<strong> coriander</strong> finely, including the stalks (save a few leaves for garnish!)</p><p>Add the<strong> chopped coriander</strong> to a <strong>pestle & mortar</strong> with a pinch of<strong> salt</strong> and a small splash of <strong>water</strong></p><p>Grind the <strong>coriander</strong> to a paste, then add 2 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[3 tbsp]</span><span class=\"text-danger\"> [4 tbsp]</span> <strong>olive oil</strong> – this is your <strong>coriander oil</strong></p><p>Tip: Don't have a pestle and mortar? Just chop the coriander finely and mix it with the oil!</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1654600743324-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1654600743324-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
